This just didn't feel like the lads to me. And that's a shame.

Up next, Frusciante returns and we get probably the album I grew up with the most as we hit their final 90s release, and man they seem to really love a certain state don't they?
full_text(utf-8): b"This just didn't feel like the lads to me. And that's a shame.\n\nUp next, Frusciante returns and we get probably the album I grew up with the most as we hit their final 90s release, and man they seem to really love a certain state don't they?"

full_text: What I've always admired about them is that they're willing so much to change, so I'm not gonna dismiss this just cause it's different-whether you love or hate the band, you can't really say they sound homogenous. Every album has been a little different too me.
full_text(utf-8): b"What I've always admired about them is that they're willing so much to change, so I'm not gonna dismiss this just cause it's different-whether you love or hate the band, you can't really say they sound homogenous. Every album has been a little different too me."

full_text: I'm sure it has its fans-and I appreciate them playing to their truth and getting a lot darker, and there was probably a pressure to not seem like a one trick pony after Blood Sugar fucking exploded-but none of the songs really grabbed me and I mostly found it flat and maudlin
full_text(utf-8): b"I'm sure it has its fans-and I appreciate them playing to their truth and getting a lot darker, and there was probably a pressure to not seem like a one trick pony after Blood Sugar fucking exploded-but none of the songs really grabbed me and I mostly found it flat and maudlin"

full_text: -but he's not the only thing that makes them special. It's their killer, brain melting catchy songs, sharp bass lines, lyrical strength and sense of personality. And I really feel the latter is lacking in OHM
full_text(utf-8): b"-but he's not the only thing that makes them special. It's their killer, brain melting catchy songs, sharp bass lines, lyrical strength and sense of personality. And I really feel the latter is lacking in OHM"

full_text: And I don't wanna be one of those guys who's like "THE CHILIS ARE NOTHING WITHOUT JOHN FRUSCIANTE!!!!!") cause I don't believe that at all. I love what John brings to the band and him and Chad Smith were a shot in the arm when they needed it-
full_text(utf-8): b'And I don\'t wanna be one of those guys who\'s like "THE CHILIS ARE NOTHING WITHOUT JOHN FRUSCIANTE!!!!!") cause I don\'t believe that at all. I love what John brings to the band and him and Chad Smith were a shot in the arm when they needed it-'

full_text: And I know they were going through dark shit, and they got a new guitarist who wasn't acclimated to their old sound (this isn't a knock on Dave Navarro-he's a great musician and seems to really respect the guys, I just don't know if I feel he's a right fit for them)
